#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/transform/copy_scale.rst:4
msgid "Copy Scale Constraint"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/transform/copy_scale.rst:6
msgid ""
"The *Copy Scale* constraint forces its owner to have the same scale as "
"its target."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/transform/copy_scale.rst:11
msgid ""
"Here we talk of *scale*, not of *size*! Indeed, you can have two objects,"
" one much bigger than the other, and yet both of them have the same "
"scale. This is also true with bones: in *Pose mode*, they all have a "
"unitary scale when they are in rest position, represented by their "
"visible length."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/transform/copy_scale.rst:19
msgid "Options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/transform/copy_scale.rst:24
msgid "Copy Scale panel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/transform/copy_scale.rst:40
msgid "Target"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/transform/copy_scale.rst:28
msgid ""
"This constraint uses one target, and is not functional (red state) when "
"it has none."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/transform/copy_scale.rst:36
msgid "Bone"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/transform/copy_scale.rst:32
msgid ""
"If *Target* is an *Armature*, a new field is displayed offering the "
"optional choice to set an individual bone as *Target*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/transform/copy_scale.rst:36
msgid "Head/Tail"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/transform/copy_scale.rst:36
msgid ""
"If a *Bone* is set as *Target*, a new field is displayed offering the "
"optional choice of where along this bone the target point lies."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/transform/copy_scale.rst:40
msgid "Vertex Group"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/transform/copy_scale.rst:39
msgid ""
"If *Target* is a *Mesh*, a new field is displayed offering the optional "
"choice to set a *Vertex Group* as target."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/transform/copy_scale.rst:44
msgid "X, Y, Z"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/transform/copy_scale.rst:43
msgid ""
"These buttons control along which axes the scale is constrained - by "
"default, it is enabled along all three."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/transform/copy_scale.rst:48
msgid "Offset"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/transform/copy_scale.rst:47
msgid ""
"When enabled, this control allows the owner to be scaled (using its "
"current transform properties), relatively to its target's scale."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/transform/copy_scale.rst:52
msgid "Space"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/transform/copy_scale.rst:51
msgid ""
"This constraint allows you to choose in which space to evaluate its "
"owner's and target's transform properties."
msgstr ""

